One person was taken to hospital following the collision on the M74. Morning crash causes delays for motorists One person was taken to hospital following the collision on the M74.The two car accident happened around 9.00 am on October 28 on the northbound carriageway between J8 Canderside and J7 Larkhall.No serious injuries are understood to have resulted from the crash, however ambulance crews took one passenger to hospital.One lane on the M74 was blocked and heavy traffic caused delays for morning commuters for at least half an hour after the incident. 